{"id":1793,"date":"2020-10-07T14:37:27","date_gmt":"2020-10-07T14:37:27","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/parliament.imarketing.com.na\/?page_id=1793"},"modified":"2025-05-22T10:46:02","modified_gmt":"2025-05-22T08:46:02","slug":"national-assembly","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-assembly\/","title":{"rendered":"National Assembly"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1622638764190{background-color: #f4f4f4 !important;}&#8221;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;19400&#8243; img_size=&#8221;full&#8221; css_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;]The National Assembly is the legislative power of the Republic of Namibia, with the power to pass laws with the assent of the President as provided by Chapter 7, article 44 of the Namibian Constitution.<\/p>\n<p>There are 104 members in the National Assembly, as per the Namibian Constitution as amended Article 46 (1) (a) and (b). \u00a0The composition of the National Assembly shall be ninety-six (96) elected members (voting members) and eight (8) non-voting members, appointed by the President as per Article 32 (5) (c) of the Namibian Constitution.<\/p>\n<p>Voting Members of the National Assembly are elected based on party lists (article 49) and every National Assembly Continue for a maximum period of five (5) years (article 50).[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1622629703981{background-color: #f4f4f4 !important;}&#8221;]<div id=\"ultimate-heading-49046848a16bbc0cd\" class=\"uvc-heading ult-adjust-bottom-margin ultimate-heading-49046848a16bbc0cd uvc-3096 h2_bg_background\" data-hspacer=\"no_spacer\"  data-halign=\"left\" style=\"text-align:left\"><div class=\"uvc-heading-spacer no_spacer\" style=\"top\"><\/div><div class=\"uvc-main-heading ult-responsive\"  data-ultimate-target='.uvc-heading.ultimate-heading-49046848a16bbc0cd h2'  data-responsi